# NTM (multi-agent tmux harness) per-machine runtime state — rate-limit
# cooldowns, swarm pane bookkeeping, and other ephemeral coordination
# bytes that change on every tick of every agent. Previously tracked,
# but the per-second churn produces no signal in git history.
.ntm/rate_limits.json
.ntm/gemini_swarm_state.json

# Beads bad-import backups
**/.beads/*.bad_*

# Beads backup / repair / recovery artifacts that don't fit the
# `*.bak_` / `.bv.lock` / `.migration-hint-ts` shapes already
# covered above. These are produced locally by `bd`'s migration,
# 3-way merge, repair, and crash-recovery tooling and are pure
# per-machine state — the canonical source of truth is the
# committed `.beads/issues.jsonl`. None of these belong in git.
**/.beads/*.bak-*
**/.beads/*.pre_fix_*
**/.beads/*.regenerated.jsonl
**/.beads/*.clean
**/.beads/*.mixed-*
**/.beads/recovery/
**/.beads/repair-backups/
**/.beads/.write.lock
**/.beads/daemon-error

