# Generated smoke-run output roots — catch-all that complements the
# explicit per-bead list above. Any new `.<name>-smoke-artifacts/`
# dir produced by a future smoke runner is auto-ignored without
# requiring a one-line .gitignore edit per runner.
/.*-smoke-artifacts/

# Root-level junk patterns added by repo-janitor 2026-05-13.
# Each of these has a sanctioned home elsewhere in the tree:
#
#   /cx_*_benchmark     — built benchmark binaries belong in target/, not at root
#                         (a 4.2 MB ELF was committed at d006b5302; never again)
#   /asupersync_*.png   — illustration PNGs are unused; README uses .webp variants
#   /bead_*.md          — bead-specific notes belong under docs/beads/
#   /MODES_*.md         — modes-of-reasoning analysis output belongs under docs/analysis/
#   /perf_scenario_*.md — perf-scenario briefs belong under docs/perf/
#   /bug_report_*.md    — historical bug reports belong under docs/audits/
/cx_*_benchmark
/asupersync_*.png
/bead_*.md
/MODES_*.md
/perf_scenario_*.md
/bug_report_*.md
